    "This raises questions about explainability, which are particularly crucial in a clinical context.",
    "Furthermore, using LLM-based methods can increase the risk of identifying seemingly plausible yet biologically irrelevant correlations (hallucinations).",
    "Additional experiments and guardrails are necessary to provide a more guided, interpretable, and assisted experience.Although standardizing workflows improves reproducibility, long-term maintenance and updating of the system are also necessary.",
